The reverend is yet to be arrested, police said. [File, Standard]  Police in Makueni have launched a hunt for a preacher, who allegedly raped an 18-year-old girl in Kilungu on October 19.  The teenager told police that she was walking home from Kikuswi Market, when the reverend offered her a lift.  “The suspect stopped his vehicle at a secluded spot a few kilometres [from Kikuswi Market] and forced himself on the girl,” the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) said on Monday, November 8.  Police say the preacher, who ministers with the Africa Inland Church (AIC) in Kilungu, warned his victim of “dire consequences” should she report the matter.  Makueni: Cancer patients can now access drugs, treatment   DP Ruto to give Mtito-a-Ndei sex workers Sh1m  DP says youths need practical solutions to problems not stipend  Makueni man goes into hiding after raping his mum The teenager, however, narrated her ordeal to one of her teachers, prompting a police report to be filed.  The suspect remains at large. “Detectives are hunting him down,” the DCI said.   Death in a Cell: 29-year-old student allegedly committed suicide while in police custody in Makueni  Afisa Kortini: Aliyekuwa OCS Makueni ashtakiwa madai ya kuchukua hongo na matumizi mabaya ya ofisi  Makueni Governor Kibwana appeals to the striking health workers in the county to return to work By Muriithi Mugo | 2 hours ago By Muriithi Mugo | 21 hours ago By Paul Ogemba | 4 days ago By Phares Mutembei | 8 days ago